<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If your in a guild that is fighting mobs that take long periods of time to kill, as a wizard your going to have mana. Its called bards with IM3(1 , KEI(14), Gfam(4), Epic(3), Potg(6), MC3(3), SCM3(effects mana usage), and focus items. Not to even mention the FT from items your guild has given you. Thats 27(no bard or FT) to 44(bard has IM3 still no FT) STANDING regen without counting FT. Then you have mod rods, nuke robes, and necromancers all supplementing more damage and more mana.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> Yeah, but you've just listed at least four other classes you need in order to accomplish this. A ranger has her/his archery skill, bow, and quiver with unlimited arrows -- does not need to rely on other people to achieve the same results in a long term fight.<br>
